article.description: Lindsay Whalen scored 22 points and  Janel McCarvell had 13 rebounds to lead Minnesota past Wisconsin-Green Bay 75-55.
article.headline: McCarvell racks up 17 pts., 13 boards, 4 blocks
article.linkText: McCarvell leads Minnesota past Wisc. Green Bay
article.story:
MINNEAPOLIS (Ticker) -- Lindsay Whalen scored 22 points and 
Janel McCarvell had 13 rebounds to lead No. 8 Minnesota past
Wisconsin-Green Bay 75-55.

Whalen dished out eight assists and McCarvell finished with 17
points and four blocks for Minnesota (8-0), which led, 36-33, at
halftime.

Freshman Jamie Brobock provided four steals and 11 points off
the bench for the Golden Gophers, who outscored Wisconsin-Green
Bay 40-14 in the paint.

Liz Podominick pulled down seven rebounds for Minnesota, which
shot 56 percent from the field and leads the nation in field
goal percentage.

Abby Scharlow scored a game-high 26 points for the Phoenix, who
connected on all seven free throw attempts during the contest.

Tricia Grassell and Nicole Soulis each scored 12 points for
Wisconsin-Green Bay (5-4), which dropped its fourth straight.
